  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SOKPE Livestock and Beekeeping Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmer households, Women, Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Theoretical and hands-on training in beekeeping, grasscutter management and poultry production. Training in project management and record keeping.
Training in compost preparation. Training on leadership skills development.  Training on the 12 HPI cornerstones. Training on gender equity. HIV/AIDS awareness creation. Farmer to farmer visitation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project targets three communities in the Volta region of Ghana&#x2014;Kpedze, Anyinawase and Sokode-Etoe&#x2014;and will directly assist 119 families. Seventy-four families will receive a total of 370 beehives with beekeeping equipment, and the remaining 45 families will receive a total of 225 grasscutters and 45 cages. Each family will also receive 20 laying chickens. Recipients will also receive training in beekeeping, grasscutter management, agroforestry, gender equity, HIV/AIDS and Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones. Capacity building in environmental resource management, enterprise development,  HIV/AIDS awareness and animal husbandry will ensure secure and sustainable livelihoods. An additional 238 families will be assisted through &#x201C;passing on the gift.&#x201D;</narrative>
  </description>
